Bandits have attacked Damaturu Village, Damari, in the Birnin Gwari Local Government Area of Kaduna State on Sunday.  The bandits, on motorbikes, were said to be on a revenge mission. “They came on many motorbikes, one bike was carrying the rider and two others. They showed no mercy. They were on rampage…it was rumoured they came on a revenge mission,” a source was quoted by Vanguard. “They were looking for members of the group of Malam Abba, a very wicked and dangerous bandit leader. The Kaduna State Police Command in 2020 said they are a terrorist group, members of Boko Haram. “The killers attacked the village on Sunday. They were shooting. The villagers ran away to different directions. Read “Last Friday, many bandits died when the boys of Malam Abba fought members of another gang. Those who came to Damari this morning were on a reprisal mission. They were told that Damari and environs were under the authority of Malam Abba.”   Source Rampaging armed bandits on Tuesday attacked communities, killing 18 persons across two local government areas of Igabi and Chikun Council Areas of Kaduna State. Nine were killed in Igabi and another in Chikun local government areas, respectively. Dozens of bandits were, however, believed to have been neutralised in in the… In "News" The spate of insecurity in the country assumed a more dangerous dimension on Monday as Boko Haram insurgents made inroads into Niger State and gunmen killed two students of Greenfield University in Kaduna state. Also on Monday, the Vice-Chancellor of the Federal University of Agriculture, Makurdi, Benue State, Professor Richard… In "News" …as police bust syndicate supplying food, drugs to kidnappers ABUJA - A syndicate allegedly supplying drugs, bread and other food items to bandits operating in Zaria, Kaduna State and its environs has been smashed by operatives of the FIB Intelligence Response Team (FIB-IRT).An alleged member of the syndicate, who admitted… In "Top Stories"